history.content:
If you are looking for something conceptually easier, then do CS 186 and CS 160. If you want a lighter workload, do CS 186 and CS 188. The projects in CS 160 can be very time consuming. I did CS 162 and CS 160 the same semester before and I ended up spending way more time on CS 160 projects than I did on CS 162 projects.

In my opinion, the slightly more difficult nature of CS 188 is definitely more bearable than the higher workload in CS 160, so I'd take CS 186 and CS 188 together if I were you.

I want to take two of these together with CS 162. 

It looks like CS 186 will be a lot of work this semester (same as Fall 16), I don't know how about CS 160 but I'm going to class today, it seems similar to CS 169, which is ok to me!

Any thoughts would be appreciated!
history.subject: Light courses among CS 188, 186, 160?
